nt||at|So in 4th seat, you may even pass a full opening hand without the spades. 
At IMPS, this is very IMPORTANT, and it's a pretty good idea at matchpoints, too.
The rule of 15 is used to decide whether to open in 4th seat.
Add your HCP and the number of spades you have. And if that number is less than 15.... pass the hand out!
Especially since modern bidding theory is to open with good 11 or 12 point hands, this rule is important|
