In second seat, you need to meet the "rule of 22"
South...add your HCP, the length of your 2 longest suits, and the number of Quick Tricks (QT's) together.
If that total is at least 22, then you should (probably) open in first or second seat
Your hand (south) is worth 20 "mitch points" (10 HCP + 2 QT + 8 for the number of cards in the 2 longest suits = 20)
or 18 Bergen Points and is a clear pass|
